2HeliumQ%22%3EHelium%20isn't%20a%20solid%20at%20absolute%20zero.%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22HeliumA%22%3EThe%20temperature%20slider%20shows%20melting%20and%20boiling%20points%20at%20standard%20pressure.%20Unlike%20any%20other%20element%2C%20helium%20will%20remain%20liquid%20down%20to%20absolute%20zero%20at%20normal%20pressures.%20This%20is%20a%20direct%20effect%20of%20quantum%20mechanics%3A%20specifically%2C%20the%20zero%20point%20energy%20of%20the%20system%20is%20too%20high%20to%20allow%20freezing.%20At%202.5MPa%2C%20a%20very%20high%20pressure%2C%20it%20will%20become%20solid.%20Then%20again%2C%20so%20will%20almost%20every%20other%20element.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22CaesiumQ%22%3EYou%20misspelled%20cesium%2Faluminum.%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22CaesiumA%22%3EWhen%20the%20USA%20submitted%20to%20the%20oversight%20of%20the%20International%20Union%20of%20Pure%20and%20Applied%20Chemistry%20(which%20allowed%20it%20to%20have%20some%20names%20for%20element%20104-111%2C%20but%20not%20all%20of%20them)%2C%20compromises%20were%20made.%20Aluminium%20is%20the%20British%20spelling%2C%20as%20is%20caesium.%20In%20exchange%2C%20the%20American%20spelling%20of%20sulfur%20(vs.%20sulphur)%20became%20the%20international%20standard.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22RomanQ%22%3EWhere%20are%20the%20Roman%20numeral%20group%20numbers%20like%20VIIB%3F%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22RomanA%22%3ERoman%20numerals%20for%20groups%20were%20scrapped%20in%201990%20by%20IUPAC%20because%20they're%20different%20and%20conflicting%20in%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20and%20Ptable%20has%20an%20international%20audience.%20If%20you're%20seeing%20them%20elsewhere%2C%20that%20source%20hasn't%20been%20updated%20in%20over%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22ValenceQ%22%3EWhere%20can%20I%20find%20valence%20numbers%3F%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22ValenceA%22%3EElectron-related%20properties%20can%20be%20found%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2F%23Electrons%2FOxidationStates%22%3Eoxidation%20states%20in%20the%20Electrons%20tab%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22WeightQ%22%3EIt's%20supposed%20to%20be%20atomic%20mass%2C%20not%20weight.%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22WeightA%22%3EAtomic%20weight%20is%20the%20official%20term%20used%20by%20IUPAC%20to%20refer%20to%20the%20relative%20atomic%20masses%20published%20specifically%20for%20inclusion%20in%20periodic%20tables.%20The%20term%20is%20used%20because%20they%20are%20%3Cb%3Eweighted%3C%2Fb%3E%20averages.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22ActinoidQ%22%3EIsn't%20it%20supposed%20to%20be%20Lanthan%3Cu%3Eide%3C%2Fu%3E%2C%20not%20-%3Cu%3Eoid%3C%2Fu%3E%3F%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22ActinoidA%22%3ENo%2C%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A%2F%2Fold.iupac.org%2Fpublications%2Fbooks%2Frbook%2FRed_Book_2005.pdf%22%3Eaccording%20to%20IUPAC%20%5BPDF%5D%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IR-3.5).%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22ConfigQ%22%3EThe%20electron%20configuration%20for%20an%20element%20is%20wrong.%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22ConfigA%22%3EPtable%20shows%20true%2C%20experimental%20values%20for%20electron%20configuration.%20The%20method%20of%20drawing%20arrows%20you%20learned%20in%20class%20works%20most%20of%20the%20time%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FElectron_configuration%23Other_exceptions_to_Madelung.27s_rule%22%3Ehas%20about%2020%20exceptions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ptable%20shows%20these%20exceptions%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22color%3A%20%23900%3B%20text-decoration%3A%20overline%3B%22%3Eoverlined%20in%20red%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22BlocksQ%22%3ELa%2FAc%20or%20Lu%2FLr%20should%20be%20in%20group%203%20with%20the%20d-block.%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22BlocksA%22%3EThis%20is%20hotly%20debated%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fiupac.org%2Fprojects%2Fproject-details%2F%3Fproject_nr%3D2015-039-2-200%22%3Ean%20IUPAC%20task%20force%20headed%20by%20Eric%20Scerri%20is%20dedicated%20to%20finding%20an%20answer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20IUPAC's%20secretary%20general%20suggests%20we%20not%20hold%20our%20breath%20for%20a%20quick%20resolution.%20There%20are%20merits%20to%20including%20Lu%2FLr%20or%20La%2FAc%20inline%20rather%20than%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20f-block%2C%20but%20there%20are%20also%20drawbacks.%20Unqualified%20to%20weigh%20in%20on%20these%20arguments%20and%20make%20sweeping%20conclusions%20that'll%20affect%20how%20millions%20a%20week%20see%20the%20periodic%20table%2C%20Ptable%20mirrors%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A%2F%2Fiupac.org%2Fwhat-we-do%2Fperiodic-table-of-elements%2F%22%3Eofficial%20IUPAC%20layout%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%0A%20%20%3Cdt%20id%3D%22BuyAdsQ%22%3EMy%20company%20would%20like%20to%20purchase%20advertising.%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%20id%3D%22BuyAdsA%22%3ECreate%20a%20campaign%20in%20Google%20Ads%20targeting%20this%20domain.%20I%20do%20not%20accept%20video%20ads%2C%20expanding%20ads%2C%20or%20interstitials%3B%20these%20will%20not%20run%20at%20any%20price.%20Do%20not%20contact%20me%20to%20publish%20%22articles%22%20with%20backlinks%20(blogspam)%2C%20paid%20links%2C%20or%20any%20other%20link%20schemes.%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%20%3C%2Fdl%3E%0A%0A%20%3Cbutton%20type%3D%22submit%22%3ESend%3C%2Fbutton%3E%0A%3C%2Ffieldset%3E%0A%0A%3C%2Fform%3E%0A%3C%2Fmain%3E%0A%0A%3Cfooter%3E%0A%20%3Cdl%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdt%3EAbout%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2Fdemo%22%3EWhat's%20new%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2Fabout%2F%22%3EQuestions%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2Fabout%2F%23privacy%22%3EPrivacy%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%20%3C%2Fdl%3E%0A%20%3Cdl%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdt%3EProducts%3C%2Fdt%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2Fposter%2F%22%3EPoster%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2Flessonplans%2F%22%3ELesson%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdd%3E%0A%20%20%3Cdd%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22%2F%2Fwww.patreon.com%2Foauth2%2Fauthorize%3Fresponse_type%3Dcode%26amp%3Bclient_id%3DsN8bpQO5TsIYTlhXxjS3-ZLYdtqZOHgjiPC928SlNyQLBnafLFEfj1rmMDjcnO3A%26a